&gt; &lt;OLD&gt;
&gt;
&gt; Tucson looks to Mach Kick and gently gets back to all fours to let him down.
&gt;
&gt; &quot; Sorry about that.  I guess I really got into my training exercises .  Good
&gt; thing you spoke up.&quot;
&gt;
&gt; He then turns to face Big Convoy.
&gt;
&gt; &quot; Master Yokitron trained me in both forms and then he took me aside and
&gt; trained me a bit further than what was normally taught in training academy.
&gt; Nightshift was trained along side with me, and not too many bots were given
&gt; the opportunity that we were given.  I feel a bit incomplete, like as if I&#39;m
&gt; missing a component of myself.  I always fought with Nightshift beside me
&gt; and together we would defeat our opponents.  And if Magmatron is believed to
&gt; have such training, I will have to work extra hard to keep my head above
&gt; water.  I know I can combat Rodimus but I&#39;m not so sure I can defeat
&gt; Magmatron.   Primus help us if he challenges me. Not much scares me but,
&gt; going against an impossible foe, does.&quot;

&lt;NEW&gt;

There was a nod from BIG CONVOY, &quot;I understand. Master Yokitron has a
reputation for having well trained pupils, and I am sure that once we
are free from this, you will be able to rejoin your comrade.&quot;

MACH KICK pats TUSCON on the shoulder, &quot;Yeah, I am sure that Big over
there . . . and um maybe you now . . .  will get us all out of here.&quot;

A few others nodded their heads around the room. Yes, others were
paying attention to the conversation.

CONVOY turned and began walking towards the back, &quot;Come I will show
you your recharging station, the night rotation is soon to begin.&quot; He
glanced back at TUSCON, &quot;I would imagine that tommorrow you may have
to face your first opponant.&quot;

